The paper focuses on analyzing the research productivity of men and women in the scientific-technological disciplines of the Italian university system. This falls under the broad category of computer science and interdisciplinary fields. The paper uses bibliometric analysis to examine the productivity of research personnel, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The study also looks at sectorial differences, which could be related to complex systems (cs.CY) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the study examines quantitative performance indicators, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE) or systems and control (cs.SY).
